<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1896-08-11T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1896-08-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="874" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d874">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Terrell</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Olney</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Constantinople</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1896-08-11"><hi rend="italic">August 11,
                                1896</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Poche telegraphs six Armenian naturalized citizens of the United States
                            in prison at Aleppo clamor for more food. A demand for their delivery
                            required by modus vivendi not answered. I believe they are
                            revolutionists.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Terrell.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>